    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` with `parse` and `stringify`\n\nThe implementation touches **8 locations** across the stack, following the exact same pattern as `Bun.JSON5`, `Bun.YAML`, etc.:\n\n### New Files\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Self-contained INI core parser. Line-by-line algorithm: skips blanks/comments (`;`/`#`), handles `[section]` headers (including dotted `[a.b]` → nested objects), parses `key=value` pairs with type coercion (`true`/`false`/numbers/null). Returns a `bun.ast.Expr` object. Does **not** import `src/ini.zig` (the npmrc-specific parser).\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS API wrapper: `create()` builds `{parse, stringify}` object. `parse()` calls the core parser and converts AST → JSValue via a copied `exprToJS` helper. `stringify()` uses a `Stringifier` struct: top-level scalars as `key=value`, nested objects as `[section]` headers, circular-reference detection.\n\n### Modified Files\n3. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n4. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 4 additions: lazy-property declaration, export, getter function, import alias\n5. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n6. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the hash table\n7. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` TypeScript definitions\n8. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — Tests for parse/stringify round-trips, sections, dotted-sections, comments, type coercion, circular references, error cases",
